description: Tiger Rockfish is known locally as Barred Rockfish. This photoed individual has 5 bars on the back, consistent with the species. Rarely caught in this area, as I interviewed a local whose fished for Rockfish extensively in the 1960s-80s. So, some local historical records of large adult Tigers caught within half mile.

Only out of water for the time it took to take photo. We needed to segregate various captures (or the big ones would eat the small ones) from one another the moment  beach seine came in> So we decided ID pics like this would help train volunteer net  haulers to ID and call out species so we could tally them before releasing.
patterns stays similar but colorations are quite variable in this Rockfish species.
